node.text:
To celebrate @elijahcraig Old-Fashioned Week, Lynnette Marrero (@drinksat6), bar director of Llama San (@llamasannyc), Llama Inn (@llamainnnyc) and Wonderbar (@wonderbarbeacon), shares how to make her Three Bites of the Apple, an Old-Fashioned inspired by autumn in the Hudson Valley. ⁠
Get the recipe at punchdrink.com and learn more about how you can raise an Elijah Craig Bourbon Old-Fashioned to support the bar community at OldFashionedWeek.com.
#punchpartner @elijahcraig #oldfashionedweek @rwcfusa 
#oldfashioned #cocktail #bartender

This episode supports industry workers in need by raising funds for @rwcfusa. You can make a contribution by going to the link in our profile, or heading over to @rwcfusa. To date, the Bacardi family of brands has contributed over $150,000 to aid in @rwcfusa’s ongoing relief efforts. @martinirossius will continue their support with a donation following this segment. #raiseyourspirits #drinkpunchtyb

node.text: With a base of mango brandy, paired with pineapple juice and banana cordial, The Lambeth Walk Fizz from @youngwilliamelliot at @maisonpremiere reads like a Ramos by way of the tropics. Get the recipe via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @ericmedsker

node.text: Last week we tasted through more than 40 wines, from pét-nat to piquette, to come up with a list of at least five wines we’d be happy to drink any day of the week. We had a tough time keeping it to 10. Coinciding with the rise of natural wine, the category has exploded over the past few years. So, without any further ado, head to the link in our profile for the complex, yet crushable cans that deserve a spot in your cooler this summer. Big thanks to our panel of tasters: @zacharysussman, @taliabaiocchi, @migueld1, @zwanng and Eliza Christen. #drinkpunch

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on July 28, 2021. May be an image of bottle.

node.text: It looks like any other Martini. But at @thunderboltla, the classically dry cocktail is transformed into a complex umami bomb with one sleeper ingredient: tomato water. The Liquid Picnic—a mixture of gin, vermouth, salt, pepper and clarified tomato water—"reads like a salad, drinks like a Martini.” The tomato water adds texture and subtle savory notes to the drink while working double-time as the drink’s only form of dilution. @mfcapoferri  uses a centrifuge for clarification at the Los Angeles bar, but we've got a home-friendly variation via the link in our profile. 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: Named after one of the Japanese autumn microseasons, @caermaiko's Wagtail Sings marries classic fall flavors with Japanese whisky. The member of our Bartender in Residence Class of 2021 makes a spiced pear syrup—honey, cinnamon, cloves, star anise, ginger and lemon—and stirs it with Suntory Toki, mole bitters and a barspoon of Underburg. Check out the recipe via the link in our profile. #bartenderinresidence #drinkpunch 📷: @jessattie

node.text: What does your ideal Pińa Colada look like? Back in the day, our expert panel blind-tasted 10 Piña Coladas from some of America's best bartenders to find the ultimate version. Head to the link in our profile to find out whose "air conditioning in a glass” came out on top. #drinkpunch ⁠ 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: Calling all Averna fans: @artusibar's boozy and bittersweet aperitivo is for you. In the Averna Smash, the Sicilian amaro is combined with bourbon and muddled fruits—orange, brandied cherry and walnut oil—before being shaken and finished off with bitter lemon soda water. The supporting ingredients naturally complement the Mediterranean botanicals in the amaro and play to the drink's bittersweet roots. Get the recipe via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text:
Meet Caer Maiko (@caermaiko), a member of our Bartender in Residence Class of 2021.⁠
⁠
The Austin-based bartender is on a mission to make "super Asian cocktails.” Today, Maiko works as a bartender at @drinkwellaustin and is the co-founder of @daijoubu.popup. The pop-up cocktail concept, in pre-pandemic times, toured across state lines in a retrofitted school bus serving an original menu of drinks, like Maiko's Dope Ass Midori Sour, served in a Chinese food to-go box. Across the drinks, glassware, menu design, music and décor, the pop-up boldly corrects the omission of Asian-influenced cocktails in mainstream cocktail culture. Maiko is able to weave her story into drinks that are equal parts quirky and classic.  Head to the link in our profile to get to know more about her in three drinks. #bartenderinresidence #punchdrink 📷: @jessattie⁠

node.text: Once a guilty pleasure thrown back in beach bars across America, the Miami Vice has found new relevance beyond indiscriminate vacation drinking. From New York to San Diego, bartenders are stretching the Pińa Colada meets Strawberry Daiquiri template to incorporate techniques from infusions to fat-washing. The new wave of Miami Vices, including @thirdsbk's Japanese-tropical take, the Miami Rice (👆), prove the two-tone slushy cocktail is ripe for experimentation. Head to the link in our profile for @newman_kara's story. #drinkpunch 📷: @ericmedsker

node.text: @steakbonestacey gives green juice a whole new meaning with the Margarita Verde. Incorporating green bell peppers, snap peas, parsley and celery juicy, she turns the garden produce into a "garden cordial" that is used to enhance the grassy notes of blanco tequila. Salers and lime juice round out the drink while Tabasco green jalapeno sauce gives it a little kick. Check out the recipe via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text:
Negroni-lovers, may we reintroduce the Campari & Soda? With its simple yet stylish nature, the iconic highball has never been more relevant. And whether you’re stirring one up at home, starting the evening at your favorite restaurant or looking for a last call option at a dive bar, you can count on a bottle of Campari (@campariusa #punchpartner) and cold soda water being at the ready. The intensely bubbly and bitter-forward combo has long been a favorite call drink of the industry—head to the link in our profile to find out why it’s considered by many to be “the perfect drink.”⁠
📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: Bearing all the hallmarks of refreshment—mint, fresh lime, soda water and, well, rum—the Mojito is an obvious shoo-in for the canon of summer classics. And yet, many Mojitos gracing menus today bear only a passing resemblance to the Cuban-born original. The modern Mojito, it seems, is rarely just a Mojito. Crossed with a Paloma, Cosmo or Corn 'n' Oil, the Cuban classic remains as refreshing as ever—head to the link in our profile for six mashup recipes. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: Good morning to this Green Apple Garibaldi. In this sweet-tart variation on the Italian aperitivo, freshly juiced granny smith apples meet a small measure of manzanilla sherry and blanc vermouth, which bring salinity and sweetness to the table. A small boost of citrus-forward gin ties it all together. Get the recipe via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro
